originalText.text: I was there in 2013 with only about 18 months of sobriety but a real hunger for the program. It was a profound experience to be in a room where so many alcoholics had shared their recovery. The history and traditions make up a big part of my program, and I look forward to my next visit there.

I went there having 15 days sobriety and I will NEVER go back. At first i I was welcomed warmly and invited to help myself to a cup of coffee. But as soon as I took my first sip some god awful witch started yelling at me in front of the entire room for not paying the¢.50 for it.

I am legally blind and did not see any sign. I am also broke as be dirt, having just moved out of the shelter into my apartment.

It's really sad that AA puts a value of ¢.50 on another human beings sobriety.
